title: For Sale:  9mm Jericho 941 tuned for Bullseye and IPSC competition

postcontent:
I've upgraded my IPSC shooter, and I'm looking to part ways with my ex-workhorse. This is a Jericho 941, with blued steel frame, and the full length dustcover. This is not the Magnum research Baby Eagle, though the design is identical. This is the real Israeli import. This little beauty has been my competition pistol for about 3 years - I wanted a pistol that would soak up recoil during timed shoots, and provide a consistent trigger. It weighs about 2lb, and you will feel how heavy it seems. The weight absorbs recoil nicely. To improve the trigger, I sent it off to have the action replaced with a double action only trigger, and a bobbed hammer for draws during IPSC matches. As such, it has a beautifully consistent pull for every shot. I've sighted it with a six o'clock hold at 25 yard bullseye, and point of aim bullseye at 50 yards. The bore I can't get a good photo of, but its still has the mirror shine - It is polygonally rifled. 

I've replaced the IWI grips with a set of rosewood grips, though I still have the original Israeli IWI grips with it. I've also purchase another two magazines, so the gun comes with 4 17 round mags. 

Look, I know I'm not going to get back the $875 I've dumped into this gun. I'd like to get a little cash back, and see it go to a good home. I'll do $600 for quick sale.

I bought this from someone else with the intention of making it a project gun, however, I simply don't have the time to right now and would like to pass this one along. This is a great base gun for a custom build or would make a fine range gun that has a lot of similarities to WWII 1911s. I personally never fired it, but the person I bought it from had and reported no problems unless using JHP which the 1911 was originally never designed to do. The previous owner installed a full length screw in guide rod and Wilson Combat shok buff. I have detail stripped the weapon to check for any thing that needed obvious attention and found none. The slide to frame fit is tight especially for a base model 1911 and I feel the weapon was well taken care of. There are some light handling marks on the weapon but nothing that's stands out. It will come in the original green hard case with the Springfield holster and magazine holders, 6 magazines, a Blackhawk Serpa holster, and approximately 80 loose rounds with about 10 JHP.  Feel free to email me any questions. Not looking for any trades. I will meet within 1hr of Pinehurst, I will not ship the weapon. Thanks.
